    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "The faint aroma of food in the bustling streets of Tulayan didn't do anything to quench Liam's hunger. Navigating through the roads packed with cars, stalls, and people, he tried to distance himself from interaction and trouble as much as possible; knowing that any interaction would probably cause <i>them</i> to find and recapture him. He can't afford to go back to that hellhole again. The patterns on his body had stopped glowing, and that voice in his head had ceased talking. But the rumbling of his stomach hadn't stopped. Damn him for stepping in earlier. He would've finished that soggy chicken earlier if he didn't intervene. Liam navigated through the sea of people, trying to make his way back to that soggy chicken at the trash, when he found himself by the riverside. He must've taken a wrong turn... or a series of them, for him to end up at the quiet street of Ordoñez, and not Vicencio."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "Right by the concrete barriers of the street was the banks of the Tanglaw River. The calm waters and the occasional sound of motorcycles passing by were the only sounds in this peaceful street. Beyond the river is the city of Tagalupang, laced with tall, imposing buildings filled with bright lights and advertisement boards; a stark contrast on the peaceful land of Tulayan."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Dialog",
      "Character": "Liam",
      "Dialog": "Where... where am I?",
      "Tags": ""
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
