      "Tags": ""
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "Minato laughed as he waved off, Ryo was about to retort when he felt his father's arms slung on his shoulder, guiding him and Liam back home."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "The three navigated the busy street of Vicencio, with Minato pulling Liam by the hand while Ryo following closely behind. Sooner or later, after weaving through the endless lines of people and going through a network of streets and paths, they soon find themselves on a quieter place in Tulayan. There was a faint sound of people singing karaoke at this ungodly hour of the night. The singer's voice was severely off-key, and even Ryo couldn't help but silently snicker at his neighbor's terrible singing. Liam smiled a bit at the sound. It's been a while since he had heard someone sing, and the fact that the first melody he hears after years was so horrible amused him a little bit. It was a nice break from the constant desire of perfection from where he escaped from, and helped his tense nerves relax a little bit."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Dialog",
      "Character": "Minato",
      "Dialog": "Alright, Liam! Here's our home!",
      "Tags": ""
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "Liam looked at the house in front of him. It was a humble abode made from a combination of different materials - cement, wood, metal sheets. The window on the second floor of the two-storey house was open, a small clothesline with a school uniform, a few sets of t-shirts, and some pants. There was a piece of fabric hung on the window frame with some emblem painted on them. The bright city lights of Tagalupang across the river reflected on the wet street, the blinding LED billboards faintly illuminating the walls of the houses facing the river. It wasn't much, but it was more than what he'd had in years, a living, breathing home."
    }
